		<item>
		<title>13 Online Events in June for Your Virtual Calendar</title>
		<link>https://brainstation.io/blog/13-online-events-in-june-for-your-virtual-calendar</link>
				<pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2020 18:13:40 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[BrainStation]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Events]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[events]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://brainstation.io/blog/?p=11895</guid>
				<description><![CDATA[<p>The tech world may have moved online in recent months, but there are plenty of virtual events planned this month to fill your calendar with inspiring, thought-provoking content. </p>
<p>Here are 13 online events in June you won’t want to miss.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://brainstation.io/blog/13-online-events-in-june-for-your-virtual-calendar">13 Online Events in June for Your Virtual Calendar</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://brainstation.io/blog">BrainStation® Blog</a>.</p>
]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>The tech world may have moved online in recent months, but there are plenty of virtual events planned this month to fill your calendar with inspiring, thought-provoking content.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Here are 13 online events in June you won’t want to miss.</p>



<h2><strong>Learn About Diversity in Tech</strong></h2>



<p>We’ve spoken before about how to encourage <a href="https://brainstation.io/blog/diversity-in-leadership-building-a-culture-for-women-to-succeed">diversity and inclusion</a> in the workplace.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Here are two events to discuss and learn more about how to help women and people of color succeed in the workplace.&nbsp;</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img src="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/05142014/photo-gallery-1.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-11904" srcset="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/05142014/photo-gallery-1.jpg 420w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/05142014/photo-gallery-1-300x225.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px" /><figcaption>BrainStation panel event</figcaption></figure></div>



<h4>Women in Leadership: Shaping Stronger Pathways</h4>



<p>While career opportunities for women have increased dramatically over the years, representation in the C-suite is far from parity, with only 21 percent of positions filled by women. At what point does this gap occur and why? And how do we work together, across generations and leadership levels, to create stronger pathways for women in the workplace?</p>



<p>Join BrainStation for a cross-generational conversation with industry leaders to explore these questions and discuss the ways we can continue on the road to equality. <a href="https://brainstation.io/event/online-women-in-leadership-june2020">Sign Up</a>&nbsp;</p>



<h4>Let&#8217;s Talk: A BPTN Conversation on Race, Privilege, and Tech</h4>



<p>Black Professionals in Tech (BPTN) is hosting a chat in partnership with LinkedIn on how we can be allies with Black tech employees in North America. Donna Alexander and Greg Butler will share and discuss how racism manifests itself within tech, how to address anti-black racism in the workplace, and what companies can do to support their employees.&nbsp;<a href="https://bptn-ca.zoom.us/meeting/register/tJAofu-gpj8oHdOazBFl6f0iqtY0bPfObUu_">Join</a></p>



<h2><strong>Celebrate Pride</strong></h2>



<p>Pride month is here, and while there won’t be any physical parades, there are a plethora of free online events that you can attend. Here are two that caught our attention.&nbsp;</p>



<h4>Out in Tech Talks: Career Edition</h4>



<p>The job market is particularly tough right now, and Out in Tech wants to make sure LGBTQ+ tech professionals are ready to take on the next opportunity. This free, half-day workshop is entirely focused on helping you find your next job, with amazing speakers from Nike, LinkedIn, Stack Overflow, and more!&nbsp;<a href="https://outintechtalks.splashthat.com/">RSVP</a></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/05142410/Screen-Shot-2020-06-05-at-2.23.32-PM.png" alt="" class="wp-image-11906" srcset="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/05142410/Screen-Shot-2020-06-05-at-2.23.32-PM.png 910w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/05142410/Screen-Shot-2020-06-05-at-2.23.32-PM-300x102.png 300w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/05142410/Screen-Shot-2020-06-05-at-2.23.32-PM-768x260.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 910px) 100vw, 910px" /></figure>



<h4>Lunch &amp; Learn with Tenniel Brown</h4>



<p>Tenniel Brown of the Centre of Anti-Oppressive Communication will be hosting 45-minute training sessions on LGBT2Q+ and Allyship 101 to provide guidance on language and identities from an intersectional lens, as well as strategies to help foster a diverse, welcoming community.&nbsp;<a href="http://pridetoronto.com/lunchandlearn">Register</a></p>



<h2><strong>Network at Major Tech Conferences</strong></h2>



<p>Want to attend a more splashy virtual event? Some of the biggest tech events have made the shift online to become global events. Everything from tech conferences like Collision and design-focused conferences like UXRC.</p>



<h4>Collision Conference</h4>



<p>By now, cities like Toronto are familiar with the tech giant Collision Conference. This year they’re offering a three-day virtual conference, with leading panelists like Ariana Huffington, Brad Smith,&nbsp;Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus, Margaret Atwood, and over 450 more.&nbsp;<a href="https://collisionconf.com/">Get Tickets</a></p>



<h4>LiveWorx</h4>



<p>LiveWorx20 is claiming the title of “the definitive event for digital transformation,” with content on augmented reality, the internet of things, robotics, and more. This virtual event boasts that this game-changing conference will help technologists innovate at scale and spur transformation that helps drive outcomes. <a href="https://www.liveworx.com/">Register</a></p>



<h4>UXRC</h4>



<p>The world&#8217;s largest UX Research conference is now online. The two-day event is for anyone who loves UX research, whether you’re a Designer, Product Manager, or just looking to learn about innovative UX. They have a packed schedule, so find the talks that interest you! <a href="https://uxrconference.com/">Get Tickets</a></p>



<h4>Spark +AI Summit</h4>



<p>Spark and + AI Summit aims to help solve some of the worlds’ biggest problems –&nbsp;with data. The massive, free conference goes on for five days, includes training, keynote speakers, and will be attended by thousands of engineers and leaders in big data.&nbsp;<a href="https://databricks.com/sparkaisummit/north-america-2020">Register</a></p>



<h2><strong>Develop Your Digital Skills</strong></h2>



<p>Learn something new from home. There’s never been a better time to upskill and these events will help you deepen your marketing and design knowledge.</p>



